-------->Introduction To CSS
        ----> CSS Stands for Cascading Style Sheet.
        ----> CSS is the language we use to style an HTML document.
        ----> CSS describes how HTML elements should be displayed.
        Example basic CSS structure{
            <code>
            
                <style>
                
                    body {
                    background-color: lightblue;
                    }

                    h1 {
                    color: white;
                    text-align: center;
                    }

                    p {
                    font-family: verdana;
                    font-size: 20px;
                    }
                
                </style>

            </code>

        }


--------> Selectors In CSS {
                -->Id Selector("#")----> U can select element by his id. also ids are Unique.

                -->Class Selector(".")----> U can select element by using his classname.classes are not unique U can style multiple element by giveing them same class.

                -->Element Selector("Ex. p,h1,button,etc...")---> U can select element by there tagname.but it will be select universaly that element.
}



